column2: A few dead bluegills - debris floating.
Somewhat less murky.  Scummy near shoreline.
No blue herons.  Only 2 wood ducks.  Lake iced over 11/14/2002.  Ice out 4/14/2003.
Sunny and breezy. Lake level is up some.
sunny. Green- dirty- good for boating only.
August 7 - 1.85 inches of rain. August 11 - 4.5 inches of rain. August 12 - 1 inch of rain.
1.25 inches of rain. Lake very high.
September 16 - 2 inches of rain. September 23 - 2.75 inches of rain. Total Rain for the summer - 30 inches.
Stained water which unusal for Barber Lake-- due to rains in past year
May 31 and June 1 very windy. Today clear and a little wind. Brownish cast to water is less each time I sample
2 inches rain on 6/17 and 18 (total). today clear. water is clear and green with algae visible
Sunny- air temp 80 degrees. Day after 4th--boat traffic  did not increase turbidity
Max air temps past week ranged from high 80's to low 90's. had 3/4 inch rain on 7/16 and  1-3/4 inch rain on 7/19 with strong storms. Today sunny and warm with air temp of 85 at 11:00 am
Strong Storms on 8/01 and 02 with 3.75 inches rain. Today clear and slightly breezy with algae visible in water
Sunny. Sampled at 11:00 am had somewhat low D.O. at surface. Probably due to time of day and major algal bloom. Bluegreen accumulating on surface of windblown bays.
Cold- sunny and breezy. Air temp 58 degrees at 11:00 am
sunny- cloudless skies- air temp 70. Number of cold nights . No stratification
Returned from Illinois on 3/23. Ice was off and neighbor indicated ice off was about 3/15. Very warm late winter. Today sunny with air temp of 62 degrees
No wind- no clouds and air temp 58 degrees
breezy- air temp 70 degrees- partly cloudy
sunny- slight breeze- air temp 65 degrees

column1: ice on lake for 111 days- first sign of ice off was 3/20/2012 - earliest ever

column2: partly cloudy- breezy- air temp 80 degrees
Parly Cloudy- air temp 80 degrees- slight breeze
Breezy- no clouds- wam air temp of 80 degrees
Sunny and bright- no clouds; breezy
Partly Cloudy- Calm and Air Temperature72 degrees
Sunny- slight breeze- air temp 72 degrees
Partly cloudy- breezy- algae visible in water
Water was brownish in color and murky. Probably due to high lake level and  tannins in heavy winter snow and rainfall runoff.
sunny and calm; ice off on May 3rd- 2014 (ice on date was Nov 15- 2013)
very clear water -- collector's personal best reading ever; calm; sunny
